## ===============================================================
## MakeIt // HQ — environment template
## ===============================================================
## Copy to .env.local (NEVER commit) and fill in real values.
## When the Supabase keys are missing the app runs in DEMO MODE
## with mock data and the cookie-based invite-code login. All other
## services individually fall back to no-ops when their keys are
## absent — see notes on each block.
##
## Bring-up order (see docs/SETUP.md for the full walkthrough):
##   1. Supabase   — required, unlocks everything
##   2. VAPID      — required for Web Push (run: npm run vapid:generate)
##   3. Anthropic  — unlocks AI program generation + form-check review
##   4. Stripe     — unlocks billing
##   5. Resend     — transactional email (coach review notifications)
##   6. OAuth      — Google / Apple (configured in Supabase dashboard,
##                   not here — see SETUP.md)


## ---------------------------------------------------------------
## 1. Supabase  — REQUIRED for connected mode
## ---------------------------------------------------------------
## Find these in https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/_/settings/api
##   - URL          → Project URL (https://<ref>.supabase.co)
##   - ANON_KEY     → "anon public" — safe to expose to the browser
##   - SERVICE_ROLE → "service_role" — server-only, bypasses RLS
##                    Used by the Stripe webhook + admin scripts.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=


## ---------------------------------------------------------------
## 2. Web Push  (VAPID)  — REQUIRED for push notifications
## ---------------------------------------------------------------
## Generate the key pair once with:
##   npm run vapid:generate
## Paste the output into here. Same values for dev + prod is fine,
## but rotating in prod invalidates every existing subscription.
NEXT_PUBLIC_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY=
VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY=
VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY=
VAPID_SUBJECT=mailto:hello@makeit.dk


## ---------------------------------------------------------------
## 3. Anthropic  — unlocks AI features
## ---------------------------------------------------------------
## Used by:
##   - Onboarding program generator (Claude Sonnet 4.6)
##   - Form-check video review (when the coach pipeline calls it)
##   - Nutrition AI suggestions
## When unset, rule-based fallbacks are used. Get a key at
## https://console.anthropic.com → Keys.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=


## ---------------------------------------------------------------
## 4. Stripe  — REQUIRED for paid tiers
## ---------------------------------------------------------------
## Test keys live at https://dashboard.stripe.com/test/apikeys.
## When STRIPE_SECRET_KEY or STRIPE_PRICE_CREW is missing, the
## checkout/portal buttons just show a "demo" banner.
##
## After creating products in the dashboard, paste their price IDs
## (the ones starting with `price_...`) below.
##   crew         = monthly Crew membership
##   one_on_one   = 1:1 coaching add-on
##
## Webhook setup: in the dashboard, point a webhook at
##   https://<your-domain>/api/stripe/webhook
## subscribed to: checkout.session.completed,
## customer.subscription.created/updated/deleted. Copy the signing
## secret into STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET.
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
STRIPE_PRICE_CREW=
STRIPE_PRICE_ONE_ON_ONE=


## ---------------------------------------------------------------
## 5. Resend  — transactional email
## ---------------------------------------------------------------
## Without these, send actions silently skip. Sign up at resend.com.
## RESEND_FROM_EMAIL must be from a domain you've verified in Resend
## (or use 'onboarding@resend.dev' for testing — only sends to your
## own account email).
RESEND_API_KEY=
RESEND_FROM_EMAIL=
RESEND_REPLY_TO=


## ---------------------------------------------------------------
## 6. OAuth (Google + Apple)
## ---------------------------------------------------------------
## NOT configured here — set in the Supabase Dashboard under
## Authentication → Providers. This file just enables the buttons
## in the login UI when the providers are toggled on remotely.
## See docs/SETUP.md → "OAuth providers" for the full walkthrough.
